From 9ca9df5d5cc0b23fd5edfdf39d817d375cb78ecc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 17:34:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] odb/refs: complete helper backend vtables

Implement the remaining helper backend callbacks that were
previously stubbed.

Ref callbacks implemented:
  - remove_on_disk: sends "remove" command to helper
  - rename_ref: read + create + delete via transaction
  - copy_ref: read + create via transaction
  - reflog_exists: sends "reflog-exists <refname>"
  - for_each_reflog_ent: parses "reflog-read" response
  - for_each_reflog_ent_reverse: collects and replays in reverse
  - delete_reflog: sends "reflog-delete <refname>"

ODB callbacks implemented:
  - begin_transaction: sends "odb-transaction-begin", returns
    transaction with commit callback that sends
    "odb-transaction-commit"

New protocol commands:
  - remove, reflog-read, reflog-append, reflog-exists,
    reflog-delete, odb-transaction-begin, odb-transaction-commit

Callbacks that remain as justified no-ops:
  - create_reflog: implicit on first append
  - reflog_expire: delegated to helper's own GC
  - reflog_iterator_begin: no protocol command yet
  - optimize/optimize_required: helper manages itself
  - fsck: delegated to helper
  - ref_iterator_seek: create new iterator instead
  - read/write_object_stream: buffered get/put sufficient
  - read/write_alternate: helper is self-contained

Signed-off-by: Aaron Willoughby <aaron@omniband.org>
